---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Arnav's Writing Quest" active="about">

<main class="wrap single">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About the Quest</h1>

    <p>
      A personalised 60-day writing program for <strong>Arnav Kashyap</strong>,
      Class 5 student in Mechelen, Belgium. The shape is Duolingo: short daily missions,
      a visible streak, XP, levels, boss days, and a coach who reads every page and writes back.
    </p>

    <p>
      Twenty-five minutes a day. Three lines on Day 1, twenty lines by Day 60. A worksheet
      gets printed, written, photographed, and uploaded — the coach reads the page, picks
      two specific things to praise, names one thing for next time, and adds a verified XP
      number to the tracker.
    </p>

    <h2>The one rule</h2>

    <p style="font-size:18px;color:var(--green-dark);font-weight:900;">
      Fluency before perfection. Confidence before correction. Momentum before neatness.
    </p>

    <p>
      In the first two weeks the coach will not mention spelling, grammar, or handwriting —
      even when they're visible — because protecting the early streak is worth more than any
      correction. The point is to make writing feel cheap and good. Polish lands later, once
      the habit is real.
    </p>

    <h2>The phases</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Days</th>
          <th>Phase</th>
          <th>Coach watches for</th>
          <th>Coach ignores</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>1–14</td><td>Fluency</td><td>Did he finish? Readable? Effort?</td><td>Spelling, neatness, grammar, punctuation</td></tr>
        <tr><td>15–21</td><td>Story Mode</td><td>Idea / story flow</td><td>Handwriting style</td></tr>
        <tr><td>22–35</td><td>Paragraph Shape</td><td>Structure + spelling</td><td>Sentence variety</td></tr>
        <tr><td>36–42</td><td>Explain</td><td>Structure + connectors</td><td>Tone</td></tr>
        <tr><td>43–49</td><td>Timed</td><td>Speed + structure</td><td>Style polish</td></tr>
        <tr><td>50–56</td><td>Opinion</td><td>Reasons + at least one example</td><td>Stylistic flourish</td></tr>
        <tr><td>57–60</td><td>Class 6 Prep</td><td>Full structure + one grammar point</td><td>Anything outside the week's goal</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>The daily loop</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Print</strong> today's worksheet (one A4 page).</li>
      <li><strong>Write</strong> for 20–25 minutes — warm-up, speed drill, main mission, self-check.</li>
      <li><strong>Photograph</strong> the page.</li>
      <li><strong>Upload</strong> to the coach and say "review".</li>
      <li><strong>Read</strong> the two praises, the one suggestion, and the XP — out loud, together.</li>
      <li><strong>Refresh</strong> the tracker. New flame. New row.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Levels &amp; badges</h2>

    <p>
      Eight levels, from Pencil Apprentice (Day 1) to Class 6 Champion (Day 60). Eight badges
      that unlock at milestones — first mission, seven-day streak, first boss, twenty
      spelling-bank words, and so on. Boss days (10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60) are longer and pay
      extra XP. Day 60 is the Grand Final.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>

    <p>
      The tracker, the worksheets, the verified reviews, and the photos of completed pages
      all live on the open web at <em>arnav.manishchandrakumar.com</em>. Arnav's writing is
      worth being proud of, so it's not hidden. Nothing sensitive is collected — there is no
      account, no login, no analytics, no third-party trackers. The whole site is a static
      bundle of HTML, CSS, JSON, and image files served by Cloudflare Pages.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top:32px;text-align:center;">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" style="background:var(--green);color:#fff;box-shadow:0 4px 0 var(--green-dark);" href="/quest">Open the tracker →</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</main>

</Base>
